People v. Sorensen (1968) 68 Cal.2d 280). 
f. Penalties 
The penalty for a misdemeanor is up to one year 
in  county  jail  and/or  up  to  a  $2,000  fine.  The  
penalty for a felony is up to one year and one day 
in state  prison  and/or  up  to  a  $2,000  fine.  (
PC  §  
270
). 
g. Statute of Limitations 
If  charged  as  a  misdemeanor,  action  must  be  
commenced within one year after commission of 
the offense. (
PC § 802) If charged as a felony, the 
action  must  be  commenced  within  three  years  
after commission of the offense. (
PC § 801). 
